    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1888-01-28T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1888-01-28T00:00:00-05:00" n="90" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d90">
                <head>No. 90.<lb/>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Bayard</persName>
                            to Mr. <persName type="to">Hall</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Extract.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department
                                    of State</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1888-01-28">
                            <hi rend="italic">January</hi> 28,
                            1888</date>.</dateline>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 543.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have received your No. 763, of the 6th
                        instant, relative to the Italian claim against Salvador 5 also your telegram
                        of the 25th instant.</p>
                <p>I desire to express the satisfaction with which the Department learns that
                        this question has reached an amicable adjustment, and to add that the result
                        is particularly gratifying in view of the manner in which it was
                        obtained.</p>
                <p>Awaiting your full report of the nature and extent of your good offices in
                        bringing the parties into mutual accord,</p>
                <p>I am, etc.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">T. F.
                            Bayard.</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
